# truncate

- _truncate(x)_

Answer the integer nearest _x_ toward `zero`,
that is the integer part of the number.

```
>>> 1.25.truncate
1

>>> -1.25.truncate
-1
```

Compare to `floor`:

```
>>> 1.25.floor
1

>>> -1.25.floor
-2
```

